parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tread separates from the tire
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the tire deforms on the tread surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Valve stem failure can cause sudden air loss, leading to tire blowouts, loss of vehicle control, and potentially result in accidents or fatalities.
symptoms: Air leaks from the valve stem
valve stem malfunctions at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle continues to move forward without slowing down

and the vehicle pulls to one side when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear and failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to extended stopping distances or loss of control.
symptoms: The brakes wear out too soon
grinding noises are heard when applying the brakes
and the vehicle is harder to stop.
